requiredStandards.requiredStandard:
Where a vehicle is only capable of towing a trailer which is not fitted with a service braking system, then the technically permissible towable mass of the vehicle must not exceed either of;
• half of the mass of the towing vehicle in running order,
• 750kg

Any device located within the driver’s compartment that enables the driver from the driving seat to deactivate the outside emergency controls in order to lock the service doors from outside, must meet the following requirements;
a. The outside emergency controls must be reactivated automatically either by the starting of the engine or before the vehicle reaches a speed of 20 km/h.
b. Subsequent deactivation of the outside emergency controls must not occur automatically, but require a further action by the driver.

Any device located within the driver’s compartment that enables the driver from the driving seat to deactivate the outside emergency controls in order to lock the service doors from outside, must meet the following requirements;
a. The outside emergency controls must be reactivated automatically either by the starting of the engine or before the vehicle reaches a speed of 20 km/h.
b. Subsequent deactivation of the outside emergency controls must not occur automatically, but require a further action by the driver.
